.TH "process_vm_rw_core" 9 "process_vm_rw_core" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
process_vm_rw_core \- core of reading/writing pages from task specified
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" process_vm_rw_core
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "struct iov_iter *iter "  ","
.BI "const struct iovec *rvec "  ","
.BI "unsigned long riovcnt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ","
.BI "int vm_write "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
PID of process to read/write from/to
.IP "iter" 12
where to copy to/from locally
.IP "rvec" 12
iovec array specifying where to copy to/from in the other process
.IP "riovcnt" 12
size of rvec array
.IP "flags" 12
currently unused
.IP "vm_write" 12
0 if reading from other process, 1 if writing to other process
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of bytes read/written or error code. May
return less bytes than expected if an error occurs during the copying
process.
